COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1039, L.D. 1581
315 disabled veteran when that application is accompanied by certification from the United
326 States Department of Veterans Affairs or any branch of the United States Armed Forces as
337 to the veteran's permanent disability and receipt of 100% service-connected benefits. Upon
348 request a disability placard may be issued at no fee. The Secretary of State may issue a
359 registration certificate and special designating plates for no more than one vehicle 3
460 vehicles owned by a veteran eligible under this subsection.
7 These special designating plates must bear the words "Disabled Veteran," which indicate
8 that the vehicle is owned by a disabled veteran.
9 Sec. 2. 36 MRSA §1483, sub-§12, as amended by PL 2021, c. 240, §1, is further
10 amended to read:
11 12. Certain veterans. Automobiles owned by veterans who are granted free
12 registration of those vehicles by the Secretary of State under Title 29‑A, section 523,
13 subsection 1 or 2 or who are disabled by injury or disease incurred or aggravated during
14 active military service in the line of duty and are receiving any form of pension or
15 compensation from the United States Government for total, service-connected disability.
16 A maximum of 3 automobiles owned by a veteran are exempt from the excise tax. In order
17 for an automobile to qualify for an exemption from the excise tax under this subsection,
18 the name of the qualifying veteran must appear on the automobile's certificate of title. If
19 there are multiple owners of an automobile, at least one of the owners whose name appears
20 on the certificate of title must meet the requirements of this subsection in order for the
21 automobile to qualify for the exemption;'
22 Amend the bill by adding before the summary the following:
23 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
24 takes effect when approved.'
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment specifies that a maximum of 3 automobiles owned by a veteran are
2299 eligible for exemption from registration fees and the excise tax.
30 The amendment also adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause to the bill.
